Property 3.1: Closeness propagation property. The closeness between node A and other nodes exponentially decreases with their distances. As shown in Figure 2, it can be illustrated by C(u, ki) = C(u, k1) ¬∑ Œµi‚àí1(Œµ < 1).
As shown in Figure 2, the more hops between node u and node ki, the less closeness between them. The closeness value is decreased to an extremely small value when the distance exceeds 3 hops. This relationship has been conÔ¨Årmed by other studies. Binzel et al. [6] discovered that a reduction in social distance between two persons signiÔ¨Åcantly increases the trust between them. Swamynathan et al. [34] found that people normally do e-commerce business with people within 2-3 hops in their social networks.

